<item>
            <title>[DATAREST-150] PUT vs PATCH with JPA</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-150</link>
                <project id="10901" key="DATAREST">Spring Data REST</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Github Author: mangvlad&lt;br/&gt;
Github Last-Updated: 2013-04-26T07:56:16Z&lt;br/&gt;
This issue was automatically imported from github&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using PUT method, removing any field appears to be interpreted as &quot;no change&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
This seems to be close to the expected behavior of PATCH method, not PUT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Step 1 GET /objects/o1  &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;f1&quot;:&quot;v1&quot;, &quot;f2&quot;:&quot;v2&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;Step 2 PUT /objects/o1  &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;f1&quot;:&quot;v1&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;Step 3 GET /objects/o1  &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;f1&quot;:&quot;v1&quot;, &quot;f2&quot;:&quot;v2&quot;}

&lt;p&gt;(it seems that the result should be &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;f1&quot;:&quot;v1&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
